genEquipRfuStatusEntry.description: Entry containing the data of the RFU.

genEquipRfuStatusTemperature.description: This value indicates the RFU temperature. The value depends on the represented measurement system. with genEquipUnitMeasurementSystem parameter.

genEquipRfuStatusRunningVersion.description: This value indicates the running SW version on the RFU.

genEquipRfuStatusRFUType.description: The different types of the supported RFUs

genEquipRfuStatusTxRxFreqSeparation.description: Tx to Rx frequency separation (MHz), For some RFUs the user cannot set the Tx and Rx frequencies separately (one of them affects the other one's value).

genEquipRfuStatusAutoDelayCalStatus.description: IF combining parameter - the automatic delay calibration status. Supported only for specific RFUs.

genEquipRfuStatusRFUmateCarrier.name: genEquipRfuStatusRFUmateCarrier
genEquipRfuStatusRFUmateCarrier.description: The returned value indicates the slot number of the 'copartner RFU-D carrier'. The returned value will be '-1' when the RFU is not RFU-D, or if the 'copartner RFU-D' carrier is not found.

genEquipRfuStatusRFUMinTxFreq.description: The minimum Tx frequency of the RFU that is allowed by the RFU.

genEquipRfuStatusRFUMaxRxFreq.name: genEquipRfuStatusRFUMaxRxFreq
genEquipRfuStatusRFUMaxRxFreq.description: The maximum Rx frequency of the RFU that is allowed by the RFU.

genEquipRfuStatusRFUMinRxFreq.name: genEquipRfuStatusRFUMinRxFreq
genEquipRfuStatusRFUMinRxFreq.description: The minimum Rx frequency of the RFU that is allowed by the RFU.

genEquipRfuStatusInstallation.name: genEquipRfuStatusInstallation
genEquipRfuStatusInstallation.description: Returns 'all-indoor' or 'split' according to the RFU installation.

genEquipRfuStatusBand.description: The Band of the RF-Module in GHz

genEquipRfuStatusPATemp.name: genEquipRfuStatusPATemp
genEquipRfuStatusPATemp.description: The measured temperature in celsius of the PA (Power Amplifier) of the RF module

genEquipRfuStatusTxMute.description: The mute status, whether it is on (mute) or off (un-mute) of the RF-Module

genEquipRfuStatusMaxTxLevel.description: The maximum feasible TX signal level (TSL) in dBm of the RF-Module

genEquipRfuStatusIfCombSupport.description: Indicates if the IF-Combiner function is supported

genEquipRfuStatusMinRxLevel.description: The minimum feasible RX signal level (RSL) in dBm of the RF-Module

genEquipRfuStatusMaxRxLevel.name: genEquipRfuStatusMaxRxLevel
genEquipRfuStatusMaxRxLevel.description: The maximum feasible RX signal level (RSL) in dBm of the RF-Module

genEquipRfuCfgEntry.description: This table indicates the RFU Configuration.

genEquipRfuCfgId.description: This value indicates an index of a specific RFU

genEquipRfuCfgMaxTxLevel.name: genEquipRfuCfgMaxTxLevel
genEquipRfuCfgMaxTxLevel.description: This value indicates the RFU Maximum Transmit Level Configuration.

genEquipRfuCfgATPCAdmin.name: genEquipRfuCfgATPCAdmin
genEquipRfuCfgATPCAdmin.description: ATPC configuration - Admin mode Possible values: - enable(2) - disable(3)

genEquipRfuCfgMuteTx.name: genEquipRfuCfgMuteTx
genEquipRfuCfgMuteTx.description: The required TX mute status of the RF-Module

genEquipRfuCfgRSLConnSrc.name: genEquipRfuCfgRSLConnSrc
genEquipRfuCfgRSLConnSrc.description: IF combining - RFU RSL (Received Signal Level) connector source

genEquipRfuCfgLogAdmin.name: genEquipRfuCfgLogAdmin
genEquipRfuCfgLogAdmin.description: RFU internal log file admin Possible values: - enable(2) - disable(3)

genEquipRfuCfgGreenModeAdmin.name: genEquipRfuCfgGreenModeAdmin
genEquipRfuCfgGreenModeAdmin.description: Enables/disables RFU green mode. This mode will minimize power consumption while ensuring the highest transmission power possible to get an RSL not higher than defined in the reference level genEquipRfuCfgGreenModeReferenceLevel

genEquipRfuCfgGreenModeReferenceLevel.name: genEquipRfuCfgGreenModeReferenceLevel
genEquipRfuCfgGreenModeReferenceLevel.description: RSL reference level (in dB) for green mode operation

genEquipRfuCfgATPCOverrideTxLevel.name: genEquipRfuCfgATPCOverrideTxLevel
genEquipRfuCfgATPCOverrideTxLevel.description: This parameter configures the default transmission signal level in case of ATPC override due to expiration of maximum power timer as defined in genEquipRfuCfgATPCOverrideTimeout.

genEquipRfuCfgATPCOverrideTimeout.name: genEquipRfuCfgATPCOverrideTimeout
genEquipRfuCfgATPCOverrideTimeout.description: This parameter configures the timer to be counted while in ATPC in case of maximum power transmission. If this timer expires, the system will transmit at a default level defined in genEquipRfuCfgATPCOverrideTxLevel

genEquipRfuCfgATPCOverrideTimerCounter.name: genEquipRfuCfgATPCOverrideTimerCounter
genEquipRfuCfgATPCOverrideTimerCounter.description: This parameter shows the time left in the timer defined by genEquipRfuCfgATPCOverrideTxLevel

genEquipRfuCfgATPCOverrideTimerCancel.name: genEquipRfuCfgATPCOverrideTimerCancel
genEquipRfuCfgATPCOverrideTimerCancel.description: Setting this parameter to ON will cancel the ATPC override mode. This will only be effective while in this mode i.e. the system had been transmitting at maximum power for a time longer than defined in genEquipRfuCfgATPCOverrideTxLevel and now is transmitting at the default level defined in genEquipRfuCfgATPCOverrideTxLevel. Following execution, the system will go back to normal ATPC operating mode

genEquipRfuUploadEntry.name: genEquipRfuUploadEntry
genEquipRfuUploadEntry.description: Entry containing the data of the RFU.

genEquipRfuUploadId.name: genEquipRfuUploadId
genEquipRfuUploadId.description: This value indicates an index of a specific RFU

genEquipRfuUploadSwCommand.description: This value initiates SW upload to the RFU.

genEquipRfuUploadSwStatus.name: genEquipRfuUploadSwStatus
genEquipRfuUploadSwStatus.description: This value indicates the status of the SW load operation on the RFU.

genEquipRfuUploadCounter.name: genEquipRfuUploadCounter
genEquipRfuUploadCounter.description: This parameter shows the progress (in blocks) of RFU software download

genEquipRfuSwInstallOperation.description: RFU software installation operation to be performed.

genEquipRfuSwInstallTimedInstallation.description: Determines whether the installation will be carried out after a configured timer.

genEquipRfuSwStatusCurrentState.description: Current state of the install operation.

genEquipRfuSwStatusProgress.name: genEquipRfuSwStatusProgress
genEquipRfuSwStatusProgress.description: Progress of the current install operation in percentage.

genEquipRadioStatusRadioId.description: This value is the radio ID that serves as the table Index.

genEquipRadioStatusMSE.name: genEquipRadioStatusMSE
genEquipRadioStatusMSE.description: MSE (Mean Square Error) of the Rx signal (measured in dB * 100). -9900 value (-99.00 dB) means that the signal is not locked. ~ -3500 value (-35.00 dB) is a good MSE.

genEquipRadioStatusDefectedBlocks.name: genEquipRadioStatusDefectedBlocks
genEquipRadioStatusDefectedBlocks.description: The number of counted defective radio blocks.

genEquipRadioStatusBER.name: genEquipRadioStatusBER
genEquipRadioStatusBER.description: The measured BER (Bit Error Rate) level of the modem.

genEquipRadioStatusXPI.name: genEquipRadioStatusXPI
genEquipRadioStatusXPI.description: XPI (Cross Polar Interference) level measured by the modem.

genEquipRadioStatusXPICEnabled.name: genEquipRadioStatusXPICEnabled
genEquipRadioStatusXPICEnabled.description: This parameter indicates whether an XPIC script is currently loaded.

genEquipRadioCfgRadioId.name: genEquipRadioCfgRadioId
genEquipRadioCfgRadioId.description: This value is the radio ID that serves as this table Index

genEquipRadioCfgMACHeaderCompression.name: genEquipRadioCfgMACHeaderCompression
genEquipRadioCfgMACHeaderCompression.description: The Admin state of the MAC header compression.

genEquipRadioCfgClearCounters.name: genEquipRadioCfgClearCounters
genEquipRadioCfgClearCounters.description: Setting this parameter to ON will clear the radio counters.

genEquipRadioCfgIfLoopback.name: genEquipRadioCfgIfLoopback
genEquipRadioCfgIfLoopback.description: The administrative state of the IF loopback.

genEquipRadioCfgExcessiveBERThreshold.name: genEquipRadioCfgExcessiveBERThreshold
genEquipRadioCfgExcessiveBERThreshold.description: The BER threshold that when exceeded will be considered as 'Excessive BER'.

genEquipRadioCfgSignalDegradeThreshold.name: genEquipRadioCfgSignalDegradeThreshold
genEquipRadioCfgSignalDegradeThreshold.description: The BER (Bit Error Rate) threshold that when exceeded will be considered as 'Signal Degrade'.

genEquipRadioCfgRadioAdmin.name: genEquipRadioCfgRadioAdmin
genEquipRadioCfgRadioAdmin.description: Radio Admin state (Enable,Disable) can be used in ifTable::ifAdminStatus

genEquipRadioCfgRadioOperationalStatus.name: genEquipRadioCfgRadioOperationalStatus
genEquipRadioCfgRadioOperationalStatus.description: The operational status of the radio interface.

genEquipRadioCfgRadioTrafficPrioritySche.name: genEquipRadioCfgRadioTrafficPriorityScheme
genEquipRadioCfgRadioTrafficPrioritySche.description: this parameter configures the relative priority of different traffic streams. High-tdm-over-high-ethernet gives priorities as follows: (1) TDM high priority (2) Ethernet high priority (3) TDM low priority (4) Etherenet low priority. High-Ethernet-over-tdm gives priorities as follows: (1) Ethernet high priority (2) TDM high priority (3) TDM low priority (4) Etherenet low priority. Tdm-over-ethernet gives priorities as follows: (1) TDM high priority (2) TDM low priority (3) Ethernet

genEquipRadioCfgRadioHiPriorityEthernetB.name: genEquipRadioCfgRadioHiPriorityEthernetBW
genEquipRadioCfgRadioHiPriorityEthernetB.description: this parameter configures the amount of bandwith reserved for high-priority Ethernet. It must be a number in resolution of 2.048 Mbit/s for E1 systems or 1.544 Mbit/s for T1 systems. The maximum possible capacity is given by genEquipRadioCfgRadioCurrentAvailableCapacity

genEquipRadioCfgRadioMultiRadioEnable.name: genEquipRadioCfgRadioMultiRadioEnable
genEquipRadioCfgRadioMultiRadioEnable.description: this parameter enables/disables the multi-radio feature for this radio. Notice that for the feature to work it must be configured in two adjacent radios (odd and even slots)

genEquipRadioCfgRadioMultiRadioBlockLoca.name: genEquipRadioCfgRadioMultiRadioBlockLocalTraffic
genEquipRadioCfgRadioMultiRadioBlockLoca.description: this parameter allows stopping distribution of data to different radios in Multi-Radio mode for debugging purposes

genEquipRadioCfgRadioMultiRadioBlockMate.name: genEquipRadioCfgRadioMultiRadioBlockMateTraffic
genEquipRadioCfgRadioMultiRadioBlockMate.description: this parameter allows stopping distribution of data to the radio in the mate IDU in Multi-Radio mode for debugging purposes

genEquipRadioCfgRadioCurrentAvailableCap.name: genEquipRadioCfgRadioCurrentAvailableCapacity
genEquipRadioCfgRadioCurrentAvailableCap.description: This parameter indicates the maximum possible capacity available for Ethernet. This sets a top limit for amount of high-priority Ethernet bandwidth

genEquipRadioCfgRadioMultiRadioExcessive.name: genEquipRadioCfgRadioMultiRadioExcessiveBERAdmin
genEquipRadioCfgRadioMultiRadioExcessive.description: This parameter configures whether in Multi-Radio mode data stops being distributed to the radio in case of an excessive BER condition

genEquipRadioCfgRadioMultiRadioSignalDeg.name: genEquipRadioCfgRadioMultiRadioSignalDegradeAdmin
genEquipRadioCfgRadioMultiRadioSignalDeg.description: This parameter configures whether in Multi-Radio mode data stops being distributed to the radio in case of a signal degraded condition

genEquipRadioCfgEnAlarmGenOnRslDegrade.name: genEquipRadioCfgEnAlarmGenOnRslDegrade
genEquipRadioCfgEnAlarmGenOnRslDegrade.description: TEnable/Disable alarm and trapgeneration on RSL degradationbelow user defined threshold.If enabled, trap and alarm willbe generated when current RSLlevel degrades below userdefined threshold for 5subsequent seconds. Alarm willbe cleared after RSL level staysabove the threshold for at leastanother 5 seconds. Thresholdis calculated as a nominal RSLlevel minus the degradationmargin.

genEquipRadioCfgAlarmGenRslNominalLevel.name: genEquipRadioCfgAlarmGenRslNominalLevel
genEquipRadioCfgAlarmGenRslNominalLevel.description: RSL nominal level [in dBm] foralarm and event generation.

genEquipRadioCfgAlarmGenRslDegradationMa.name: genEquipRadioCfgAlarmGenRslDegradationMargin
genEquipRadioCfgAlarmGenRslDegradationMa.description: RSL degradation margin [in dB]for alarm and eventgeneration. The margin isrelative to the nominal RSLlevel

genEquipRadioCfgLinkShutDownOnRadioFailu.name: genEquipRadioCfgLinkShutDownOnRadioFailure
genEquipRadioCfgLinkShutDownOnRadioFailu.description: This parameter enables shutting down the link and initiating automatic state propagation upon a failure in each one of the radios. Radio failure condition is determined by user configurations and can be one of the following: Radio LOF, Link ID mismatch, Radio excessive BER, Radio signal degrade, Link ID mismatch.

genEquipRadioCfgLoopbackTimeout.name: genEquipRadioCfgLoopbackTimeout
genEquipRadioCfgLoopbackTimeout.description: The timeout in minutes for automatic termination of the loopback. The value '0' refers to 'no timeout'.

genEquipRadioCfgAbcMode.name: genEquipRadioCfgAbcMode
genEquipRadioCfgAbcMode.description: TThe radio mode (multi direction or multi carrier).

genEquipRemoteRadioRadioId.description: This value is the radio ID that serves as this table Index

genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteForceMaxTxLevel.description: Command that forces the remote radio maximum Tx level (in dBm)

genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteTxFreq.name: genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteTxFreq
genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteTxFreq.description: The remote radio Tx frequancy (in MHz).

genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteRxFreq.name: genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteRxFreq
genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteRxFreq.description: The remote radio Rx frequancy (in MHz).

genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteATPCReferenceRx.name: genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteATPCReferenceRxLevel
genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteATPCReferenceRx.description: The RSL reference level for the ATPC mechanism in the remote radio.

genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteDefaultGateway.name: genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteDefaultGateway
genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteDefaultGateway.description: Default gateway of remote NE (Network Element) across this radio link.

genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteMostSevereAlarm.name: genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteMostSevereAlarm
genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteMostSevereAlarm.description: Most severe alarm of remote NE (Network Element) across this radio link.

genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteSubnetMask.name: genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteSubnetMask
genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteSubnetMask.description: Subnet mask of remote NE (Network Element) across this radio link.

genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteForceTxMute.name: genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteForceTxMute
genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteForceTxMute.description: Force the mute state of the remote unit radio interface.

genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteLinkId.name: genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteLinkId
genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteLinkId.description: The Link Id of the remote unit radio interface.

genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteATPCoverrideSta.name: genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteATPCoverrideState
genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteATPCoverrideSta.description: Remote Radio ATPC Override Timer expire state.

genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteATPCoverrideSta.description: his coomand cancel remote ATPC override state.

genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteDataLoopBackAdm.name: genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteDataLoopBackAdmin
genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteDataLoopBackAdm.description: Remote unit administrator state of data loopback.

genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteDataLoopBackDur.name: genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteDataLoopBackDuration
genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteDataLoopBackDur.description: Remote Data LoopBack Duration at remote unit[Minutes], zero for infinite loop back.

genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteGreenReferenceR.name: genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteGreenReferenceRxLevel
genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteGreenReferenceR.description: Remote Radio Green RSL reference level[dBm].

genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteGreenModeAdmin.name: genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteGreenModeAdmin
genEquipRemoteRadioRemoteGreenModeAdmin.description: Remote Unit Tx Green Mode Admin.

genEquipRadioMRMCRadioId.description: This value is the radio ID that serves as this table Index

genEquipRadioMRMCSelectedScriptIndex.description: The index of the MRMC script. The description of the script located in the genEquipRadioMRMCScriptTable.

genEquipRadioMRMCEnAlarmOnAcmProfileDegr.name: genEquipRadioMRMCEnAlarmOnAcmProfileDegrade
genEquipRadioMRMCEnAlarmOnAcmProfileDegr.description: Enable/Disable event and trapgeneration on ACM profiledegrade. When enabled and ifcurrent radio script supports Adaptive Code Modulation(ACM) event and trap will begenerated upon ACM profiledegradation below userdefinedthreshold. Alarm willbe generated only if the ACMprofile stays below thethreshold for at least 5 subsequent seconds. Alarm willbe cleared after ACM profilereturns to be above thethreshold again.

genEquipRadioMRMCScriptRadioId.name: genEquipRadioMRMCScriptRadioId
genEquipRadioMRMCScriptRadioId.description: This value is the radio ID that serves as this table Index

genEquipRadioMRMCScriptIndex.name: genEquipRadioMRMCScriptIndex
genEquipRadioMRMCScriptIndex.description: The index of the MRMC scripts.

genEquipRadioMRMCScriptProfile.description: The profile number of the script

genEquipRadioMRMCScriptProfileBitrate.name: genEquipRadioMRMCScriptProfileBitrate
genEquipRadioMRMCScriptProfileBitrate.description: The Bit rate of the MRMC profile (in Kbps).

genEquipRadioMRMCScriptAdaptivePower.name: genEquipRadioMRMCScriptAdaptivePower
genEquipRadioMRMCScriptAdaptivePower.description: 'Adaptive Power' option which is available only when operation mode is ACM-adaptive

genEquipRadioMRMCScriptReference.name: genEquipRadioMRMCScriptReference
genEquipRadioMRMCScriptReference.description: 'Reference Class' option which is available only when operation mode 'ACM-adaptive' AND 'Adaptive Power' are enabled.

genEquipRadioMRMCScriptMinProfile.name: genEquipRadioMRMCScriptMinProfile
genEquipRadioMRMCScriptMinProfile.description: 'Minimum Profile' option which is available only when operation mode 'ACM-adaptive' AND 'Adaptive Power' are enabled. It state the minimum profile level for this script.

genEquipRadioMRMCScriptAttrScriptId.description: The ID of the MRMC script.

genEquipRadioMRMCScriptAttrScriptName.description: The name that identifies the script.

genEquipRadioMRMCScriptAttrSupportACM.description: Indicates if the MRMC script supports ACM (Adaptive Coding Modulation) functionality

genEquipRadioMRMCScriptAttrStandard.name: genEquipRadioMRMCScriptAttrStandard
genEquipRadioMRMCScriptAttrStandard.description: The standard that the MRMC script is designed to comply with.

genEquipRadioMRMCScriptAttrMultiCarrier.name: genEquipRadioMRMCScriptAttrMultiCarrier
genEquipRadioMRMCScriptAttrMultiCarrier.description: Indicates whether the MRMC script support a single carrier or any kind of multi carrier.

genEquipRadioMRMCScriptAttrTxBW.description: The TX channel bandwidth (channel spacing) of the MRMC script.

genEquipRadioMRMCScriptAttrRxBW.description: The RX channel bandwidth (channel spacing) of the MRMC script.

genEquipRadioMRMCScriptAttrRxOccupiedBW.name: genEquipRadioMRMCScriptAttrRxOccupiedBW
genEquipRadioMRMCScriptAttrRxOccupiedBW.description: The RX channel occupied bandwidth of the MRMC script.

genEquipRadioMRMCScriptAttrLinkGrade.description: The link grade level that the MRMC script is designed to cope with.

genEquipRadioMRMCScriptAttrDiffGrade.name: genEquipRadioMRMCScriptAttrDiffGrade
